After an hour's delay they at last moved on, descending the hill. The fog that was dispersing on the hill lay still more densely below, where they were descending. In front in the fog a shot was heard and then an- other, at first irregularly at varying intervals trata . . . tat and then more and more regular- ly and rapidly, and the action at the Goldbach Stream began. 
Not expecting to come on the enemy down by the stream, and having stumbled on him in the fog, hearing no encouraging word fro
